On June 26, the 10-day forecast indicated low chance of rain and a high of 78 for the 5th of July.
The next day, however, called for 60%-80% of thunderstorms on July 5th, but with a high of low 80s.  

July 5.  All prognosticative indications were for wrath-of-god rain.  It poured most the day the day before.  Still, the Marriott Ranch was awesome, and with K's present (an umbrella made for two) there was naught to dampen our spirits.

At 4:00pm, Director of Ops asked me to make a call: outdoor or under the pavilion.  "Ask me again at 4:45pm", I replied.  

4:45pm - threatening clouds and no rain.  "Outside, please."  And then...

The clouds broke, the sun shined, and the most perfect day unfolded.  Convivials by Der initiated the celebration...for maids and mens alike.  

J was beautiful.  I messed up my vows...actually uttered "take my wife...please".  She just smiled at me lovingly.  

Much much more to the story, including pics.  More to come.

the Spirit of the Game took a few shots today.
last play: long throw (line drive) to JM in the end zone.  
one of theirs was lined up to intercept...and the disc airbounced over his head and back down for the winning catch.
unreal.
sweet.

dirt bears fruit
we cross the line

family, friends, and the chosen

had a haircut that...was exactly like the guy fourth from the left:
http://www.pooh.cz/upload/img/1000/galaxy_quest_3.jpg

last night, rain was 100% for today, now 0%.

matters not: she's coming home tonight.

i see oscillatory malaise-
not circadian.
since mexico
when it hit the fan.
milder now, but man.

before, it was superman:
whether flicking or stroking
<it>(still, recall the peaker-crasher)</it>
thatwithstanding, it was
all on,
all off.

then slipped on water.
gods-after all those years.
almost washed the damn bridge out.
der was there (words fail).
kept falling.
then resigning.

different: now it pisses me off.
seeing it, or its effect matters less
than keeping eyes open.
now i pull my own strings.

sleepy.
coffee seemed to do little.
ultimate game today.
wait.  last time i was sleepy
before a game
i played well.
in fact,
whenever i was sleepy 
before a game or a race
i was on like popcorn.

sleepy turns to anticipation.
being sleepy now leaves the suggestion of excitement.
odd twist.

(sorry to locals that i was not able to plan anything while there)

had convivials in coronado (did the pic turn out?)

returning.
landed at 3:11pm in DFW.  connecting scheduled to depart by 3:35pm.
no way.
people part the aisle to give me a head start.
running...no sprinting.

**no way my luggage will make it, even if i do**

people cheer me on (no kidding)

**haven't eaten, no coffee, low sugar - head splitting**

nearly the last to board.
luggage made it on, too.

then i start reading The Dark Tower II.  
without giving anything away, was the read was complemented well by the physical ordeal.

good to be home.

[Scene I: where servio drives south to dermer for some holidayzing in 2004.  speeding ticket - 3 months to pay.  no prob.  promptly lost the ticket.  called nc dmv 1 month later.]

"hi.  i'd like to pay a speeding fine."
"sure.  ticket number?"
"i lost it."
"no problem - i can search for it with your name"
...
"sir - we have no record of you having a speeding ticket."
"er...how do i pay it?"
"sorry, sir - i don't see your name after multiple searches.  can you try again in a few weeks - maybe it hasn't propogated in our system yet."
"ok."

[Scene II: one month later, same script, same actors - additional discourse follows]

...
"so, what do i do to pay the fine?"
"try calling back in a couple weeks."
"what if you still can't find me then and 3 months passes - will that mean i won't have to pay it?"
"i'm sure it will turn up."

[Scene III: almost 3 months after incurring the speeding ticket, servio gets a letter from a law office regarding the ticket offering to assist in contesting the ticket.  call to law office]

"hello.  got your letter."
"yes.  you may not be at fault - we can help you..."
"i'm sorry.  what?"
"we can help you contest this ticket..."
"how do know that i got a ticket in NC?"
"we are provided certain information to proactively assist..."
"wait - the DMV does not have me on record as having a ticket - where did you get your information from?"
"i am sorry - can't share that."
"thanks.  i need to call the DMV now.  goodbye."

[ring ring]

"NV DMV - how can i help you?"
"can i pay you now for the speeding ticket?"
"of course."
"so, why did the law offices of slim-shady get this before you did?"
"do you really think that's in my script of responses?"
"no."
"thanks for your payment.  c'mon back to NC now, ya hear?"

[Scene IV: where servio applies for a dc license at a dc dmv after moving from va in 2005]

"sorry sir, the NC DMV has flagged your license.  we can not issue one now."
"er, what do i need to do?"
"call'em."

[ring ring]

"NC DMV - how can i help you?"
"i paid you - what gives?"
"oh, so sorry sir.  one moment...that should do it - have the DC DMV try again."
[bara-bing]

[Scene V: presently, where servio applies for a va license at a va dmv after moving from dc]

"sorry sir, the NC DMV has flagged your license.  we can not issue one now."
"er, what do i need to do?"
"call'em."

[ring ring]

"ahem."
"oh, so sorry sir.  one moment...that should do it - have the VA DMV try again."
"what happened?"
"heh heh, looks like the courthouse forgot to give us the {tchk} a-ok - sometimes that happens."
"er, ok.  here's the va fax number so you can se--"
"ho no, sir - we do not send any faxes - it's policy."
"er, so what do i do now?"
"wait about 48 hours - try again."
"can you send me a letter just in case?"
"nope.  have a nice day."

---

waiting.

one big day, many little ones.  phone calls to various northern virginia establishments.  reading 'zines (well, surfing past inordinate amount of ads).  deicions: with sun on nape or carpet 'neath foot.  personal vs. prefab: can we bring our own convivials (oh, say a Yukon Cornelius Belgian and even an English Whitbread - nudge nudge)?  

cuba, mexico, ireland, scotland - a mix of blood and dirt.  d talks of oxytocin action - i see j and feel the same, of the same.

with the right amount of the right beer, who knows...
glumbert - Best wedding first dance ever

ruminating on friend's zymurgistical talents, disconnection from the work work work, and wrapping good times up under a tree.  

...

too much garbage and baggage in this ma-cheen.  memory leaks (what is up with FF 2.0.0.11 anyway?), who knows what in the reg, apps no longer used: time to start tabula rasa.

downloaded all necessary and sufficient apps - i think, including drivers.  
back in a few hours (with any luck at all).

Update:

A handful of people were in the know for some time.  Kelly tops.  Der and Mer, of course.

Gawd - someone should document that it is in fact possible for the masses to keep a secret when the secret' worth keeping.

Two teams, both know and are known by her, scrimmaging.
Under the lights.
Friends from other worlds observe.
"Does anyone have anything to share?"
"Yeah", I said
"Just wanted to say that you all are celebrating our one year anniversary - we met on the field playing Ultimate..."

/* applause and smiles */

"...and now, after one year, I'd like to say that
She was my captain

/* slight gasp from the crowd */

my best friend
my roommate
my harshest critic
and staunchest supporter
and i hope she will to continue to be so
for a long time"

/* opens a small, cherry wood box */

"  "

/* drops to one knee */

/* comes back up after getting a look */

"Yes."

/* a chorus of clapping, cheers, hoots, laughter, smiles */

/* pop! champagne flows */
/* field lights go out */

the story has just begun.

but hey baby,
it's the thought that counts.
when i move away,
you cry;
when i come close
you shy.
where do you come from
when i'm closest to you?
where do you go
when i couldn't be farther?
now, you look back
and try to see what was there.
tendrils of regret
and the lure of 
living in the past:
keeps you from
digging in and 
rising up.

that was so yesterday - 
today, it's dirt and petals.

"at least the one i've had"

*one* of the most beautiful things i have ever heard.

10 years ago (well, in a month or two anyway)
der said, "bring her in, it's my bar."
mer musta knew we would not only hit it off,
but continue to imbue each other with
flavors of candor - anima and animus.

then, this furry creature too young to even meow
walks inquisitively up to me (on der's bar)
and approves of my choice of convivial libation
and accepts the namesake.

o-yasumi nasai.

Dean & Deluca loop.  70 miles.

ok, 102K - not M. but still: not bad. took a *long* time, since i was mostly toodling. went from the shop to mason neck park: http://www.gmap-pedometer.com/?r=1097880. lost my thought somewhere along the way. liberating. call it zen, what you will. plenty of time for ratiocination tomorrow. not sure i can recommend the route. still, the 1/2 way point is serene.
convivial: relating to feasting, drinking, and good company; festive. Convivials. Convivial libation. A man, a horse. Huddlestons. Murphy's. That cool corner place Hillsborough (?). Samichlaus.

Contrary to popular
mis-information
"Exit Only"
doesn't mean you can't re-enter
the interstate.

But it'd make a good story...

Many lifts beget trust,we
can trust our own lift, many
times.  His vehicle lifts our
hearts when our minds shatter;
his wake heals our hearts when
our minds forget.
"This is the one we came for!"

Last calls are rung for sons
& mothers
Home is a place we're always
approaching
Never quite found our way
Glasses stacked & tabs tallied
Never dull the heart
But words in ears
Are the breath of life
And the dreams brought to
Our spririts
Will find their graves
on our pillows
